Chunk 2 — Django Debug Toolbar 🔍

First the why — and this one's for you specifically, Akash.

You already know SQL well. And you know your Django ORM lines like:

WeatherReading.objects.order_by('-recorded_at').first()

...secretly turn into real SQL under the hood. You figured that out yourself.

The Debug Toolbar is the tool that shows you that hidden SQL. It's a panel that slides onto the side of your page in the browser and reveals:

- The exact SQL every ORM line became
- How many queries ran (and if any are wasteful duplicates)
- How long each took, cache hits, and more

It only appears in development — never for real users.

So it's like X-ray glasses for your page — you see the machinery behind the pretty HTML.

That's the why. Ready to install it? (3 quick steps.)
